>\\n<li>1.1 Understanding AI: Definitions and Concepts</li>\\n<li>1.2 Historical Development of AI</li>\\n<li>1.3 Current AI Technologies and Applications</li>\\n<li>1.4 AI Trends and Future Directions</li>\\n<li>1.5 AI Terminology and Jargon for Policy Makers</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 2: AI in Governance and Public Policy ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>2.1 Role of AI in Government and Public Services</li>\\n<li>2.2 Case Studies of AI in Public Administration</li>\\n<li>2.3 AI for Regulatory Compliance and Enforcement</li>\\n<li>2.4 Challenges of AI Adoption in Government</li>\\n<li>2.5 Policy Considerations for AI Implementation</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 3: Ethical, Social, and Human Rights Implications of AI ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>3.1 Principles of AI Ethics</li>\\n<li>3.2 Bias, Fairness, and Discrimination in AI Systems</li>\\n<li>3.3 Privacy and Data Protection</li>\\n<li>3.4 Socio-Economic Impacts of AI</li>\\n<li>3.5 AI and Human Rights</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 4: Legal and Regulatory Frameworks for AI ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>4.1 Overview of AI Regulations Globally</li>\\n<li>4.2 Data Governance and Privacy Laws</li>\\n<li>4.3 Intellectual Property Rights in AI</li>\\n<li>4.4 Liability and Accountability in AI Systems</li>\\n<li>4.5 Developing AI Policies and Legislation</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 5: AI Risk Management and Security ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>5.1 AI Safety and Security Challenges</li>\\n<li>5.2 Risk Assessment and Management Strategies</li>\\n<li>5.3 Cybersecurity and AI</li>\\n<li>5.4 Ensuring Reliability and Resilience</li>\\n<li>5.5 Incident Response and Crisis Management</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 6: Economic Impacts of AI ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>6.1 AI and the Future of Work</li>\\n<li>6.2 AI&#8217;s Role in Economic Growth</li>\\n<li>6.3 Supporting AI Innovation and Entrepreneurship</li>\\n<li>6.4 AI in Developing Economies</li>\\n<li>6.5 Addressing Economic Inequalities</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 7: AI Strategy, Implementation, and Collaboration ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>7.1 Developing National AI Strategies</li>\\n<li>7.2 Building AI Capabilities in the Public Sector</li>\\n<li>7.3 Public-Private Partnerships in AI</li>\\n<li>7.4 Funding and Investment in AI</li>\\n<li>7.5 Monitoring, Evaluation, and Continuous Improvement</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 8: Shaping the Future of AI Policy", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>8.1 Emerging AI Technologies and Trends</li>\\n<li>8.2 International Cooperation on AI Governance</li>\\n<li>8.3 AI and the Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs)</li>\\n<li>8.4 Public Engagement and Transparency</li>\\n<li>8.5 The Future of AI Policy Making</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Optional Module: AI Agents for Policy Maker ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>1. Understanding AI Agents</li>\\n<li>2. Case Study</li>\\n<li>3. Hands-On Activity</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}], "feature_image_jpg_url": "https://wsrv.nl/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aicerts.ai%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F03%2FAIC_AI-Policy-Maker.svg&output=jpg", "who_should_enroll_points": [{"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Public Administrators:</strong> Enhance your skills in using AI tools to streamline policy implementation, optimize public sector operations, and drive impactful results.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Business Analysts:</strong> Equip yourself with the skills to leverage AI for policy analysis, predict outcomes, and inform strategic decisions across sectors.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Students &amp; New Graduates:</strong> Gain a competitive advantag