ge": "https://www.aicerts.ai/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/Adversarial-Robustness-Toolbox.png"}], "description": "<p>The AI+ Security Level 3™ course provides a comprehensive exploration of the intersection between AI and cybersecurity, focusing on advanced topics critical to modern security engineering. It covers foundational concepts in AI and machine learning for security, delving into areas like threat detection, response mechanisms, and the use of deep learning for security applications. The course addresses the challenges of adversarial AI, network and endpoint security, and secure AI system engineering, along with emerging topics such as AI for cloud, container security, and blockchain integration. Key subjects also include AI in identity and access management (IAM), IoT security, and physical security systems, culminating in a hands-on capstone project that tasks learners with designing and engineering AI-driven security solutions.</p>\\n", "lms_course_id": "502", "course_tagline": "Master the Future of Cybersecurity with AI-Driven Solutions ", "certificate_code": "AT-2103", "feature_image_url": "https://www.aicerts.ai/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/AIC_AI-Security-Level-3-1.svg", "certificate_overview": {"exam_format": "50 questions, 70% passing, 90 minutes, online proctored exam ", "prerequisites": "Completion of AI+ Security Level 1™ and 2™, Advanced Python programming, ML and Cybersecurity Knowledge, Cloud/Container expertise, Linux/CLI mastery. ", "included_items": "Instructor-led OR Self-paced course + Official exam + Digital badge ", "certificate_duration": "<ul>\\n<li><span data-contrast=\\"auto\\"> Instructor-Led: 5 Days (live or virtual) </span></li>\\n<li><span data-contrast=\\"auto\\"> Self-Paced: 40 hours of content</span></li>\\n</ul>\\n"}, "certification_modules": [{"certification_module_title": "Module 1: Foundations of AI and Machine Learning for Security Engineering ", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>1.1 Core AI and ML Concepts for Security</li>\\n<li>1.2 AI Use Cases in Cybersecurity</li>\\n<li>1.3 Engineering AI Pipelines for Security</li>\\n<li>1.4 Challenges in Applying AI to Security</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 2: Machine Learning for Threat Detection and Response", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>2.1 Engineering Feature Extraction for Cybersecurity Datasets</li>\\n<li>2.2 Supervised Learning for Threat Classification</li>\\n<li>2.3 Unsupervised Learning for Anomaly Detection</li>\\n<li>2.4 Engineering Real-Time Threat Detection Systems</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 3: Deep Learning for Security Applications", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>3.1 Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for Threat Detection</li>\\n<li>3.2 Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) and LSTMs for Security</li>\\n<li>3.3 Autoencoders for Anomaly Detection</li>\\n<li>3.4 Adversarial Deep Learning in Security</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 4: Adversarial AI in Security", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>4.1 Introduction to Adversarial AI Attacks</li>\\n<li>4.2 Defense Mechanisms Against Adversarial Attacks</li>\\n<li>4.3 Adversarial Testing and Red Teaming for AI Systems</li>\\n<li>4.4 Engineering Robust AI Systems Against Adversarial AI</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 5: AI in Network Security", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>5.1 AI-Powered Intrusion Detection Systems</li>\\n<li>5.2 AI for Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) Detection</li>\\n<li>5.3 AI-Based Network Anomaly Detection</li>\\n<li>5.4 Engineering Secure Network Architectures with AI</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 6: AI in Endpoint Security", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>6.1 AI for Malware Detection and Classification</li>\\n<li>6.2 AI for Endpoint Detection and Response (EDR)</li>\\n<li>6.3 AI-Driven Threat Hunting</li>\\n<li>6.4 Implementing Lightweight AI Models for Resource-Constrained Devices</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 7: Secure AI System Engineering", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>7.1 Designing Secure AI Architectures</li>\\n<li>7.2 Cryptography in AI for Security</li>\\n<li>7.3 Ensuring Model Explainability and Transparency in Security</li>\\n<li>7.4 Performance Optimization of AI Security Systems</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 8: AI for Cloud and Container Security", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>8.1 AI for Securing Cloud Environments</li>\\n<li>8.2 AI-Driven Container Security</li>\\n<li>8.3 AI for Securing Serverless Architectures</li>\\n<li>8.4 AI and DevSecOps</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 9: AI and Blockchain for Security", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>9.1 Fundamentals of Blockchain and AI Integration</li>\\n<li>9.2 AI for Fraud Detection in Blockchain</li>\\n<li>9.3 Smart Contracts and AI Security</li>\\n<li>9.4 AI-Enhanced Consensus Algorithms</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 10: AI in Identity and Access Management (IAM)", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>10.1 AI for User Behavior Analytics in IAM</li>\\n<li>10.2 AI for Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)</li>\\n<li>10.3 AI for Zero-Trust Architecture</li>\\n<li>10.4 AI for Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 11: AI for Physical and IoT Security", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>11.1 AI for Securing Smart Cities</li>\\n<li>11.2 AI for Industrial IoT Security</li>\\n<li>11.3 AI for Autonomous Vehicle Security</li>\\n<li>11.4 AI for Securing Smart Homes and Consumer IoT</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 12: Capstone Project - Engineering AI Security Systems", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>12.1 Defining the Capstone Project Problem</li>\\n<li>12.2 Engineering the AI Solution</li>\\n<li>12.3 Deploying and Monitoring the AI System</li>\\n<li>12.4 Final Capstone Presentation and Evaluation</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Optional Module: AI Agents for Security level 3", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>Understanding AI Agents</li>\\n<li>Case Studies</li>\\n<li>Hands-On Practice with AI Agents</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}], "feature_image_jpg_url": "https://wsrv.nl/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aicerts.ai%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F10%2FAIC_AI-Security-Level-3-1.svg&output=jpg", "who_should_enroll_points": [{"who_should_enroll_point": "<ul>\\n<li><b>Cybersecurity Professionals</b>: Individuals looking to enhance their skills in compliance and security management.</li>\\n</ul>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Risk Management Specialists</strong><strong>:</strong> Those interested in improving risk assessment and mitigation strategies using AI.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>IT Security Analysts</strong><strong>:</strong> Analysts seeking to integrate AI technologies into their security practices and frameworks.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Tech-Savvy Leaders:</strong> IT managers or security architects aiming to future-proof their organizations with AI-enhanced compliance, governance, and security practices.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Compliance Officers</strong><strong>:</strong> Professionals responsible for ensuring adherence to regulatory standards who want to leverage AI for compliance processes.</p>\\n"}], "why_this_certification_matters": [{"key_points": "IoT Security Using AI", "key_points_detail": "Understanding how to protect IoT devices with AI-driven solutions to prevent vulnerabilities. "}, {"key_points": "Deep Learning for Threat Detection ", "key_points_detail": "Expertise in leveraging deep learning algorithms for advanced threat analysis and response. "}, {"key_points": "AI-Driven Network Security", "key_poi