IF Practitioner’s Playbook: Implementing Responsible and Secure AI", "certificate_code": "AC 102", "feature_image_url": "https://www.aicerts.ai/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/AIC_Practitioners-Playbook-for-RSAIF.svg", "certificate_overview": {"exam_format": "", "prerequisites": "Familiarity with AI systems and basic security principles", "included_items": "", "certificate_duration": "<p>8 Hours</p>\\n"}, "certification_modules": [{"certification_module_title": "Module 1: AI Security Foundations – Responsible Development & Secure Design", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>1.1 Overview of AI Security Challenges</li>\\n<li>1.2 Secure Design Principles</li>\\n<li>1.3 Best Practices for Secure AI</li>\\n<li>1.4 Hands-On: Threat Modeling Workshop</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 2: AI Threat Models", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>2.1 Introduction to Threat Modeling</li>\\n<li>2.2 Creating an AI Threat Model</li>\\n<li>2.3 Tools for Threat Modeling</li>\\n<li>2.4 Case Study: AI in Autonomous Vehicles</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 3: Secure AI SDLC (Software Development Lifecycle)", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>3.1 SDLC Overview</li>\\n<li>3.2 AI-Specific Security Measures</li>\\n<li>3.3 Continuous Monitoring &amp; Feedback Loops</li>\\n<li>3.4 Hands-On: Integrating Security in AI Development</li>\\n<li>3.5 Use Case: AI Fraud Detection System</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 4: Enforcement & Model Integrity", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>4.1 Securing AI Systems Post-Deployment</li>\\n<li>4.2 Model Integrity and Auditing</li>\\n<li>4.3 Hands-On: Implementing RBAC</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 5: Audit Readiness & Red-Teaming", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>5.1 Preparing AI Systems for Audits</li>\\n<li>5.2 Red-Teaming for AI Systems</li>\\n<li>5.3 Hands-On: Red-Teaming Simulation</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 6: Toolkits & Automation", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>6.1 Introduction to AI Security Tools</li>\\n<li>6.2 Automating AI Security and Compliance</li>\\n<li>6.3 Hands-On: Tool Integration</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}], "feature_image_jpg_url": "https://wsrv.nl/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aicerts.ai%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F10%2FAIC_Practitioners-Playbook-for-RSAIF.svg&output=jpg", "who_should_enroll_points": [{"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>AI Security Professionals</strong> looking to enhance their practical skills in securing AI systems and managing risks across the AI lifecycle.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Data Scientists and Engineers</strong> who want to integrate security into AI model development and deployment pipelines.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>AI Governance and Compliance Officers</strong> seeking to gain a deeper understanding of security measures and regulatory requirements for AI systems.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Tech Leads and Managers</strong> who oversee AI projects and need to ensure secure and ethical AI practices within their teams.</p>\\n"}, {"who_should_enroll_point": "<p><strong>Cybersecurity Experts</strong> aiming to specialize in AI-specific threats and enhance their threat modeling and risk mitigation strategies.</p>\\n"}], "why_this_certification_matters": [{"key_points": "Hands-On Expertise", "key_points_detail": "Provides practical tools and strategies for implementing secure AI practices, enabling professionals to address real-world challenges in AI security."}, {"key_points": "Enhanced Threat Management", "key_points_detail": "Equips professionals with techniques to identify, assess, and mitigate AI-specific threats such as adversarial attacks and data poisoning."}, {"key_points": "Practical Security Integration", "key_points_detail": "Guides the integration of security measures throughout the AI 