to Bitcoin</li>\\n<li>1.4 Bitcoin Vs Blockchain</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 2: Understanding Bitcoin Blockchain Mechanics", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>2.1 Deep Dive into Components</li>\\n<li>2.2 Lifecycle of a Bitcoin Blockchain Transaction</li>\\n<li>2.3 Understanding P2P Networks</li>\\n<li>2.4 The Mystery of Consensus Protocols</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 3: Bitcoin Script Decentralized Apps", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>3.1 Bitcoin Scripting Basics</li>\\n<li>3.2 Script Types: P2PKH and P2SH</li>\\n<li>3.3 Script Operations</li>\\n<li>3.4 Multisig Transactions</li>\\n<li>3.5 Escrow Services</li>\\n<li>3.6 Time-Locked Contracts</li>\\n<li>3.7 Atomic Swaps</li>\\n<li>3.8 Payment Channels</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 4: Blockchain Frameworks", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>4.1 Ethereum and its Ecosystem</li>\\n<li>4.2 Introduction to Other Frameworks</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 5: Advanced Blockchain Concepts", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>5.1 Layer 2 Scaling Solutions</li>\\n<li>5.2 Privacy Enhancements</li>\\n<li>5.3 Smart Contracts on Bitcoin</li>\\n<li>5.4 Sidechains and Drivechains</li>\\n<li>5.5 Atomic Swaps</li>\\n<li>5.6 Schnorr Signatures and Taproot</li>\\n<li>5.7 Decentralized Autonomous Organizations (DAOs)</li>\\n<li>5.8 Tokenization and Asset Issuance</li>\\n<li>5.9 Cross-Chain Interoperability</li>\\n<li>5.10 Governance and Protocol Evolution</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 6: Cryptocurrencies: Trading, Regulations, and Compliance", "certification_module_description": "<ol>\\n<li>6.1 The Financial Side of Cryptos</li>\\n<li>6.2 Dive into ICOs, DAOs, NFTs, and DeFi</li>\\n<li>6.3 Legal and Compliance</li>\\n</ol>\\n"}, {"certification_module_title": "Module 7: Bitcoin Real-world Applications", "certification_module_description": "<